			<ns0:name>dmichael@chromium.org</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/dmichael@chromium.org/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">How are you getting the input events from the main pepper thread to your app's main thread (assuming your using a different one)? Unfortunately, resource reference counting is not thread-safe, so you have to copy everything you need out of the event and stick the data in a thread-safe queue (or have a queue going back to the main thread for release). Is there any chance you're losing events due to some race condition?

Is it a Windows-only problem, or just not tested on other platforms?</ns0:content><ns0:updated>2011-09-23T15:42:32.000Z</ns0:updated><ns0:published>2011-09-23T15:42:32.000Z</ns0:published><ns2:updates /><ns0:title>Comment 2 by dmichael@chromium.org</ns0:title><ns0:link href="http://code.google.com/p/nativeclient/issues/detail?id=2285#c2" rel="alternate" type="text/html" /><ns0:link href="https://code.google.com/feeds/issues/p/nativeclient/issues/2285/comments/full/2" rel="self" type="application/atom+xml" /></ns0:entry>